{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 60,
  "title": "第六十章（居位）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "治大國，若烹小鮮。以道蒞天下。亓鬼不神，非亓鬼不神也。亓神不傷人也，非亓神不傷人也。聖人亦弗傷也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "夫兩不相傷，故德交歸焉。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "鮮，魚。烹小魚不去腸、不去鱗、不敢撓，恐其糜也。治國煩則下亂，治身煩則精散。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 9,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以道德居位治天下，則鬼不敢以其精神犯人也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 21,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "其鬼非無精神也，非不入正，不能傷自然之人。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 49,
          "end": 49
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "非鬼神不能傷害人。以聖人在位不傷害人，故鬼不敢干之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "鬼與聖人俱兩不相傷也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 21,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "夫兩不相傷，則人得治於陽，鬼神得治於陰，人得保全其性命，鬼得保其精神，故德交歸焉。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不擾也，躁則多害，靜則全真，故其國彌大，而其主彌靜，然後乃能廣得眾心矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 49,
          "end": 49
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "治大國則若烹小鮮，以道蒞天下則其鬼不神也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 21,
          "end": 22
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "神不害自然也，物守自然則神無所加，神無所加則不知神之為神也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 49,
          "end": 49
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道洽則神不傷人，神不傷人則不知神之為神。道洽則聖人亦不傷人，聖人不傷人則不知聖人之為聖也。猶云，不知神之為神，亦不知聖人之為聖也。夫恃威網以使物者，治之衰也。使不知神聖之為神聖，道之極也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "神不傷人，聖人亦不傷人，聖人不傷人，神亦不傷人。故曰，兩不相傷也。神聖合道，交歸之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
